Mediterranean menu that features well cooked entrees with plenty of filling vegetarian items that don't involve soy or meat substitutes. The food is what you would eat on a healthy Mediterranean diet with flavors like zaatar and harissa and fragrant Olive oil.  At our table, the pan seared brussel sprouts with zaatar were particularly good. The highlight of the cauliflower dish was the leben. Would also recommend the salmon. The muhamara comes with laffa, and the fries were straight from the fryer.  Sisters also has a bar alongside the sit down restaurant in front and in back. Of course, sisters hosts Brooklyn maqam hangout and balkan jams every week, drawing people for the outstanding middle Eastern music even more than the food. Their live performances are at an enjoyable volume, and they attract serious talent. It's a small space though and they can be packed, so better to reserve a table.

I generally dislike Sisters, though I have had (and it is possible to have) good experiences here. Some of the food is great, some of it is really not. For the prices, I'd expect more consistency and effort. Went on a date, had the coffee cocktail, and it was delicious.

Sisters has a beautiful ambiance and decor. I went with a friend on a weekend night and we waited about 30 minutes for a seat (no problem, we just got drinks and stood). The hostess was wonderful and helped us out the whole time we were waiting. We ending up sitting at the corner of the bar by the wall. It's actually really nice to sit at the bar here; not awkward and uncomfortable like a lot of places. We decided we didn't need to wait for a table so we just stayed at the bar the whole time. The bar chairs have backs which I really appreciate.  Service was great, there were 3 bartenders/servers working their respective corners of the bar so they weren't in your face the whole time.  My friend and I ordered fried green tomatoes,  a veggie burger and the risotto. It was just ok - a good quantity but the quality was a bit lacking, and it was overpriced. The drinks were pretty good - not the best cocktail I've ever had but not the worst. I would recommend this place for a date over drinks, since it's a great place to sit and talk for a long time and not super loud or crowded.  I would come back just because I live close by, but there are better and less expensive places to spend an evening.

I chose Sisters to go to for my birthday for the ambiance and decor but I couldn't imagine just how amazing it would be in person. I had the salmon and a Pink Orpheus cocktail and my boyfriend had a burger and fries with a 100 Hand Slap cocktail. We both thoroughly enjoyed everything and can't wait to return!
